## Uploading objects to S3

To upload a new file to my bucket, I first ran the command "sudo touch /tmp/test.txt" This command creates a new file named test.txt inside folder /tmp

The second command I ran was "aws s3 cp /tmp/test.txt s3://nextwork-vpc-project-buchi" This command will move the file test.txt to the s3 bucket nextwork-vpc-project-buchi

The third command I ran was "aws s3 ls s3://nextwork-vpc-project-buchi," which validated that the newly created file test.txt is present in the bucket alongside the other files there

